# Trivy ignore list for the Phase 7.6 GHCR release scan.
#
# Policy: HIGH/CRITICAL fixable vulns fail the release (see
# .github/workflows/release.yml, Phase 7.6 step). Each entry below is a
# tracked exception — a vuln whose "Fixed Version" in the trivy DB refers
# to a component we don't actually ship (typically a daemon-side CVE
# mis-attributed to the Go client SDK that shares a module path).
#
# Full upstream-blocked list lives in docs/security-audit.md. When a CVE
# here gets a real fix in the Go SDK we consume, remove it from this
# file — do NOT suppress by severity or package name, only by exact ID.

# github.com/docker/docker — Moby daemon CVEs mis-attributed to the Go
# client library. The module path `github.com/docker/docker` is used by
# both the daemon repo and the Go client SDK; trivy's DB records "Fixed
# Version: 29.x" against the daemon release, but there is no Go SDK v29
# tag (latest is v28.5.2+incompatible as of 2026-04-12, verified via
# `go list -m -versions github.com/docker/docker`). The Go client
# cannot patch a daemon-side authorization bypass by bumping itself.
# Tracked in docs/security-audit.md as upstream-blocked R-001.
CVE-2026-34040
